6 shall be so constructed to\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 accommodate either receptacles or output cables with optional receptacles.  Each circuit shall have a separate equipment ground bus and neutral bus for each.  Equipment ground buses shall not be shared between output circuits.  The CP\_
6 shall be capable \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 f a maximum of twelve (12) duplex circuits or six (6) simplex circuits and shall accommodate booth locking and non\_locking receptacles up to the maximum rating of the CP\_
6.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs20\insrsid16188244 
\par \page \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 4.12\tab Manual Restart }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\fs20\insrsid16188244 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 (OPTIONAL)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs20\insrsid16188244 
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                The Manual Restart option provides\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  protection to the applied load against electrical disturbances that are        
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                 associated with power outages. When a power outage occurs, current and voltage can take wild swings
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                 around nominal. The applied load has no pro\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 tection against the types of disturbances unless it has an 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                 UNINTERRUPTIBLE power supply feeding it. The Manual Restart option requires an operator to manually reset 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                 the input main circuit breaker in the event of a breaker \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 trip. This allows an orderly startup of the applied load,
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0                 preventing possible damage to the connected equipment.
\par 
